-- Think Environmental Wins $28 Million Malaysian Biomass Project Contract
-- B y   B a l d a v e   S i n g h
-- 2010-12-30T01:55:36Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-30/think-environmental-wins-28-million-malaysian-biomass-project-contract.html
The Think Environmental Co. , a
Singapore renewable energy project developer, won an 87 million-
ringgit ($28 million) contract to construct a biomass plant in
Pahang, Malaysia.  The contract for the 10-megawatt project at Jengka was
awarded by FTJ Bio Power Sdn., a joint venture between Malaysian
state-owned utility  Tenaga Nasional Bhd.  and  Felda Palm
Industries Sdn. , Think Environmental said in a statement
yesterday.  Construction will start in the first quarter of next year
and is expected to be completed by the last quarter of 2012. The
plant will use empty fruit branch as feedstock.  To contact the reporter responsible for this story:
